 March 21 at Madhusudan Mancha; 5.45 pm: Parag presents Basanta Utsav (an evening of Tagore songs and recitation accompanied by dance). Participants include Pradip Ghosh and Bratati Bandyopadhyay in recitation; Abhirup Guha Thakurta, Pramita Mullick, Swastika Mukhopadhyay, Pubali Mukhopadhyay, Achin Mukhopadhyay, Subrata Sengupta, Shilpi Aditya Basu and Mrinmoy Roy in songs; and Polly Guha, Anita Mullick, Koushik Chakraborty, Khinoor Sen Barat, Sanchita Batabyal, Vandana Alase Hazra, Samapti Das, Arkadev Bhattacharya and artistes of Indian Cultural Ensemble in dance. 

 March 21 amp; 24 at Max Mueller Bhavan; 7 pm: Ranan presents Crossings: Exploring the facets of Lady Macbeth. Concept amp; direction: Vikram Iyengar. Created with performers from the Indian classical dance and music, folk music and drama: Archana Ramaswamy (Bharata Natyam), Debashree Bhattacharya (Kathak), Suman Sarawgi (Manipuri), actress Dana Roy, Nageen Tanvir (vocal) and Siddhartha Bhattacharya (percussion). 

 March 26 amp; 27 at Rabindra Sadan; 6 pm: Kalamandalam?s Sangeetotsav 2005 features dances and audio-visual performances. 

